The paper proposes a deep learning approach for image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of fully convolutional networks and image similarity suggest that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of dual-guidance and other techniques to improve the network's performance, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on brain image registration, which suggests that it could also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category.
